{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "5d882284-4bd0-41db-8b3d-827f754c5413", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "5. IT, Data & Security Policies", "section": "5.3 Cybersecurity Incident Response", "subsection": "5.3.2 Incident Response Process", "raw_content": "Upon receipt of an incident report, the Security Operations Centre follows NexaCorp's NIST CSF-aligned Incident Response Plan (IRP-001): Identification: Validate the incident, assess initial scope, and assign severity level (P1\u2013P4). Containment: Isolate affected systems, revoke compromised credentials, and preserve evidence. Eradication: Remove malicious code, close exploited vulnerabilities, and remediate root cause. Recovery: Restore systems from clean backups, verify integrity, and gradually return to normal operations. Post-Incident Review: Conduct blameless post-mortem within 10 business days of containment; update IRP accordingly. Regulatory Notification: In cases involving personal data breaches, the Legal and Privacy teams will determine notification obligations within 72 hours (GDPR) or applicable local law timelines.", "type": "text", "text": "Part: 5. IT, Data & Security Policies\n            Section: 5.3 Cybersecurity Incident Response\n            Subsection: 5.3.2 Incident Response Process\n            Upon receipt of an incident report, the Security Operations Centre follows NexaCorp's NIST CSF-aligned Incident Response Plan (IRP-001): Identification: Validate the incident, assess initial scope, and assign severity level (P1\u2013P4). Containment: Isolate affected systems, revoke compromised credentials, and preserve evidence. Eradication: Remove malicious code, close exploited vulnerabilities, and remediate root cause. Recovery: Restore systems from clean backups, verify integrity, and gradually return to normal operations. Post-Incident Review: Conduct blameless post-mortem within 10 business days of containment; update IRP accordingly. Regulatory Notification: In cases involving personal data breaches, the Legal and Privacy teams will determine notification obligations within 72 hours (GDPR) or applicable local law timelines."}, "page_content": "Part: 5. IT, Data & Security Policies\n            Section: 5.3 Cybersecurity Incident Response\n            Subsection: 5.3.2 Incident Response Process\n            Upon receipt of an incident report, the Security Operations Centre follows NexaCorp's NIST CSF-aligned Incident Response Plan (IRP-001): Identification: Validate the incident, assess initial scope, and assign severity level (P1\u2013P4). Containment: Isolate affected systems, revoke compromised credentials, and preserve evidence. Eradication: Remove malicious code, close exploited vulnerabilities, and remediate root cause. Recovery: Restore systems from clean backups, verify integrity, and gradually return to normal operations. Post-Incident Review: Conduct blameless post-mortem within 10 business days of containment; update IRP accordingly. Regulatory Notification: In cases involving personal data breaches, the Legal and Privacy teams will determine notification obligations within 72 hours (GDPR) or applicable local law timelines.", "type": "Document"}}